WEBVTT

00:02.635 --> 00:04.670
(Funky Disco plays)
♪My Name Is Cleveland Brown

00:04.672 --> 00:06.872
♪And I Am Proud To Be

00:06.874 --> 00:09.174
♪Right Back In My Hometown

00:09.176 --> 00:12.011
♪With My New Family

00:12.013 --> 00:14.146
♪There's Old Friends
And new friends ♪

00:14.148 --> 00:16.382
♪And Even A Bear

00:16.384 --> 00:18.817
♪Through Good Times
And bad times ♪

00:18.819 --> 00:20.319
♪It's True Love We Share

00:20.321 --> 00:22.654
♪And So I Found A Place

00:22.656 --> 00:24.823
♪Where Everyone Will Know

00:24.825 --> 00:27.159
♪My Happy Mustached Face

00:27.161 --> 00:31.096
♪This Is  <i>The Cleveland Show.♪</i>

00:35.335 --> 00:36.402
(Grunts)

00:39.072 --> 00:41.673
Bowling!

00:41.675 --> 00:43.242
Bowling!

00:43.244 --> 00:44.710
See, baby?

00:44.712 --> 00:47.846
I told you bowling wasn't just
for alcoholics and dirtbags.

00:47.848 --> 00:49.348
You're right, mama.

00:49.350 --> 00:51.383
And they've got free wind!

00:51.385 --> 00:52.551
(Air Whooshing)

00:52.553 --> 00:54.153
(Shouting Happily)

00:56.056 --> 00:57.856
Excuse me.

00:57.858 --> 00:59.358
Do you have
little kid balls?

00:59.360 --> 01:00.392
Who told you?

01:00.394 --> 01:02.094
Oh, bowling balls for kids.

01:02.096 --> 01:05.064
Yes, I have those
and not the other kind.

01:05.066 --> 01:07.699
I can also program
the gutter rails.

01:07.701 --> 01:10.035
They'll only come up when
it's your kid's turn.

01:10.037 --> 01:12.037
That way, he'll never
throw a gutter ball.

01:12.039 --> 01:14.106
Oh, that's great, thanks.

01:16.076 --> 01:18.944
(Inhales Deeply)

01:18.946 --> 01:21.046
You made
another kid's day, carl.

01:21.048 --> 01:24.383
Go ahead and take a hundred
dollars from the register.

01:24.385 --> 01:26.785
(Register Beeps, dings)

01:26.787 --> 01:29.388
Come on, baby!

01:29.390 --> 01:32.724
You can do all things in
christ who strengthens you.

01:32.726 --> 01:33.792
A'ight.

01:34.561 --> 01:36.795
(Grunts)

01:50.910 --> 01:51.944
(Gasps)

01:51.946 --> 01:54.313
I am good at doing bowling!

01:54.315 --> 01:56.315
♪

02:15.768 --> 02:18.770
That was amazing, rallo!

02:18.772 --> 02:21.440
I'm gonna get us
some rubb'ry nachos,

02:21.442 --> 02:24.543
'cause you beat me
fair and square.

02:26.446 --> 02:28.147
Did you see that wink?

02:28.149 --> 02:30.949
That's the signal to burn down
the senior center.

02:30.951 --> 02:32.317
(Explosion, People screaming)

02:32.319 --> 02:35.020
(Sirens Wailing)

02:37.290 --> 02:40.125
So, rallo got to
go bowling with donna,

02:40.127 --> 02:43.629
and I had to take junior
and roberta to fuddruckers.

02:43.631 --> 02:44.796
But then it...

02:44.798 --> 02:46.331
Shut up, shut up, shut up!

02:46.333 --> 02:47.533
Sorry, cleveland.

02:47.535 --> 02:49.301
I suddenly couldn't
hear one more thing

02:49.303 --> 02:51.003
about you and your
blended family.

02:51.005 --> 02:52.337
What happened to us?

02:52.339 --> 02:53.872
Things have gotten
predictable.

02:53.874 --> 02:55.974
Yeah, the spark is gone.

02:55.976 --> 02:57.776
Oh, yeah?

02:58.811 --> 03:02.381
♪

03:11.191 --> 03:13.192
(Music Stops)

03:13.194 --> 03:15.694
Ah, I guess
we are predictable.

03:15.696 --> 03:19.531
Look at us,
several couples of schmoes.

03:19.533 --> 03:21.700
Well, maybe things
aren't quite as electric

03:21.702 --> 03:23.502
as when we were newly-friends,

03:23.504 --> 03:25.571
but we can reignite
our old spark.

03:25.573 --> 03:28.540
We just need to
spice things up somehow.

03:28.542 --> 03:29.675
Let's have a baby.

03:29.677 --> 03:31.176
Are you insane?!

03:31.178 --> 03:33.045
You want to bring
a child into this?!

03:33.047 --> 03:35.747
We have got to fix us!

03:37.684 --> 03:40.052
Well, if skydiving
doesn't put the spark

03:40.054 --> 03:42.921
back in our relationship,
nothing will.

03:42.923 --> 03:45.257
It's worked on none
of     <i>the bachelor!</i>

03:50.863 --> 03:52.197
You're too heavy!

03:52.199 --> 03:54.099
One of you is
gonna have to let go!

03:59.038 --> 04:03.008
If you want to get your spark
back, you should go to paris!

04:05.445 --> 04:09.815
<i>Il pleure dans mon coeur,</i>
<i>comme il pleut sur la ville.</i>

04:11.884 --> 04:13.719
<i>Frere jacques-itch.</i>

04:13.721 --> 04:15.454
(Sighs)
This isn't working.

04:15.456 --> 04:18.457
Are you guys the ones
with lasagna?

04:21.894 --> 04:23.762
The people's champion
is here.

04:23.764 --> 04:25.731
But don't look
directly at me.

04:25.733 --> 04:27.799
Anybody want
to smell my glove?

04:27.801 --> 04:30.936
Baby, I was so proud of
your bowling yesterday.

04:30.938 --> 04:32.971
Look, I put your scores
up on the fridge,

04:32.973 --> 04:35.040
with the cute
picture junior drew.

04:36.909 --> 04:40.078
Why has no one asked me
about that drawing?

04:40.080 --> 04:42.914
Mama, you got pounded
by your own son.

04:42.916 --> 04:44.916
Like oedipus's mom,
probably.

04:44.918 --> 04:46.785
You know,
when I get big,

04:46.787 --> 04:49.621
I'm gonna buy you
a new house and a real wig.

04:49.623 --> 04:51.123
What is that, yarn?

04:51.125 --> 04:53.492
Ha! Strike, turkey!

04:56.929 --> 04:58.430
It's no use.

04:58.432 --> 05:01.166
We've tried two things we
could think of, Mr. Zimmerman.

05:01.168 --> 05:02.267
Doctor.

05:02.269 --> 05:03.935
Mm, psychologist.

05:03.937 --> 05:06.605
Our relationship
has lost its spark.

05:06.607 --> 05:09.508
Let me GUESS: You spend all
your time together in a bar.

05:09.510 --> 05:10.609
Guy's good.

05:10.611 --> 05:12.277
See, male friendships are

05:12.279 --> 05:16.281
based on only three THINGS:
Proximity, chairs and beer.

05:16.283 --> 05:18.283
I wrote about it in my book,

05:18.285 --> 05:20.819
<i>beer me, sit near me,</i>
<i>why can't you hear me?</i>

05:20.821 --> 05:22.788
But those friendships
only last

05:22.790 --> 05:24.122
about three-and-a-half years.

05:24.124 --> 05:26.024
And you've been together...?

05:26.026 --> 05:29.628
Tomorrow will make
three-and-a-half years.

05:29.630 --> 05:31.997
I'm sorry,
but your friendship is over.

05:31.999 --> 05:33.465
(All Groan)

05:33.467 --> 05:35.300
Now, would you like
to pay by check,

05:35.302 --> 05:36.968
or by letting me
hypnotize you?

05:36.970 --> 05:39.938
Full DISCLOSURE:
Things will get weird.

05:43.509 --> 05:45.010
Look.

05:45.012 --> 05:47.679
The amusement park where we
went on our first friend-date.

05:47.681 --> 05:49.648
Huh. Funky junction.

05:49.650 --> 05:51.650
Funny we'd
pass that now.

05:51.652 --> 05:53.018
Sad funny.

05:53.020 --> 05:55.153
Like billy crystal,
but funny.

05:55.155 --> 05:57.356
(Chuckles)
Remember holt was too short

05:57.358 --> 05:59.224
to ride the rocking
pirate ship?

05:59.226 --> 06:01.159
So I mauled
the operator.

06:01.161 --> 06:03.362
And then we all got drunk
and watched you bang

06:03.364 --> 06:05.897
that robot chick from
the country bear jug band.

06:05.899 --> 06:07.165
(Laughter)

06:07.167 --> 06:08.333
Yeah.

06:08.335 --> 06:11.370
Oh, so wrong,
but so funny.

06:11.372 --> 06:14.072
Like billy crystal,
but funny.

06:14.074 --> 06:18.410
(Sighs) Shame we'll never have
a moment like that again.

06:18.412 --> 06:20.412
(All Screaming)
HOLT: Mommy!

06:20.414 --> 06:22.280
CLEVELAND: Forgive me for not
driving defensively!

06:24.684 --> 06:26.351
Condemned?

06:26.353 --> 06:29.087
How could it fall apart
this much in three years?

06:29.089 --> 06:30.856
Metaphor. Park is us.

06:30.858 --> 06:33.058
Simile. Park is like us.

06:33.060 --> 06:35.227
Been taking SA.T. Prep
to meet chicks.

06:35.229 --> 06:36.728
I guess this is it, then.

06:36.730 --> 06:38.697
Our friendship has died.

06:38.699 --> 06:41.500
Like most of the '94 chargers.

06:48.608 --> 06:50.208
He's unstoppable!

06:50.210 --> 06:52.043
The crowd wondering
how he can even be related

06:52.045 --> 06:54.946
to that old leathery
bowling bag!

06:54.948 --> 06:57.516
Ha! Strike, turkey!

07:02.555 --> 07:04.122
Oh, fudge me!

07:04.124 --> 07:06.124
Ha! Already got
you busting out

07:06.126 --> 07:08.226
the kid-friendly
swear words.

07:08.228 --> 07:11.229
You know what,
you got more exes in real life

07:11.231 --> 07:12.898
than you do in bowling!

07:12.900 --> 07:14.366
Ha! Strike, turkey!

07:17.637 --> 07:18.770
Son of a fart!

07:18.772 --> 07:20.405
How we coming on that beer?!

07:20.407 --> 07:23.742
Too bad those pins
aren't wine glasses, huh?

07:23.744 --> 07:26.645
You're good at
knocking those back.

07:26.647 --> 07:27.879
Okay, this ends now.

07:33.152 --> 07:35.587
What was that?

07:35.589 --> 07:37.589
Reali-tay!

07:37.591 --> 07:39.324
Strike, turkey!

07:39.326 --> 07:41.493
Drive yourself home.

07:49.769 --> 07:51.436
Am I a terrible mother?

07:51.438 --> 07:54.439
Roberta, tell me I'm
not a terrible mother.

07:54.441 --> 07:55.774
Tell me, damn it!

07:55.776 --> 07:56.942
Mom, relax.

07:56.944 --> 07:58.810
I'm sure rallo's fine.

07:58.812 --> 08:00.278
You didn't see the
look on his face

08:00.280 --> 08:01.847
when I put down
those rails.

08:01.849 --> 08:03.615
I'm telling you,
the poor kid's

08:03.617 --> 08:05.784
whole world crumbled down.

08:05.786 --> 08:07.319
Rallo!

08:07.321 --> 08:09.788
Baby, I'm sorry
I ruined bowling for you.

08:09.790 --> 08:10.822
Don't be sorry.

08:10.824 --> 08:12.190
Just tell me
the truth.

08:12.192 --> 08:14.159
What else have you been
lying to me about?

08:14.161 --> 08:15.660
Nothing, baby, just that.

08:15.662 --> 08:17.629
That was a lie, too,
wasn't it, mom?

08:17.631 --> 08:21.500
Just like when you said this
looks exactly like a tree.

08:21.502 --> 08:24.503
This doesn't look exactly like
a tree, does it, mom?!

08:24.505 --> 08:25.670
Well, I...

08:25.672 --> 08:26.838
Answer the question!

08:26.840 --> 08:28.306
Well, technically,

08:28.308 --> 08:30.475
I suppose real trees
don't have faces.

08:30.477 --> 08:32.978
But, rallo, I love it
because it came from you.

08:32.980 --> 08:35.847
And you know I love you
a bazillion times.

08:35.849 --> 08:37.983
Is "bazillion"
Even a number?

08:37.985 --> 08:39.718
(Sighs)
I'm not sure.

08:40.987 --> 08:43.021
I'm sorry, rallo.

08:43.023 --> 08:46.358
From now on, I swear I'm only
gonna tell the truth.

08:46.360 --> 08:49.027
Your tube top makes
you look cheap.

08:49.029 --> 08:50.395
Mom!
Truth.

08:50.397 --> 08:51.696
Oh, yeah?!

08:51.698 --> 08:54.232
Well, you-- you're...

08:54.234 --> 08:57.035
(Sobbing):
You're perfect!

08:57.037 --> 08:59.404
I can't be you!

09:05.511 --> 09:07.345
Take us home,
cleveland.

09:07.347 --> 09:08.713
It's over.

09:08.715 --> 09:11.516
But our entire relationship
can't end like this.

09:11.518 --> 09:13.084
The rides are still there.

09:13.086 --> 09:14.920
How about one last hurrah,

09:14.922 --> 09:18.089
so we remember the good times,
not the bad times?

09:18.091 --> 09:19.925
Like breakup sex. Been there.

09:19.927 --> 09:22.093
Actually, had sex,
then she broke up with me.

09:22.095 --> 09:23.862
Actually, she just
broke up with me.

09:23.864 --> 09:25.697
Because she was having sex
with someone else.

09:25.699 --> 09:27.365
So, uh, yeah, breakup sex.

09:27.367 --> 09:28.433
Cleveland,
it's locked.

09:28.435 --> 09:30.101
How would we
even get in?

09:30.103 --> 09:33.204
(Roars)

09:33.206 --> 09:35.206
Huh. You're useful.

09:35.208 --> 09:36.274
When we break up,

09:36.276 --> 09:38.710
I'm definitely
finding another bear friend.

09:38.712 --> 09:40.111
Or maybe an ox.

09:40.113 --> 09:41.713
Or a really strong penguin.

09:41.715 --> 09:43.548
Oh, penguins are the worst.

09:43.550 --> 09:45.784
Don't be fooled
by their formal dress.

09:45.786 --> 09:47.085
Bunch of slobs.

09:47.087 --> 09:49.287
Cheap, misogynist slobs.

09:52.091 --> 09:53.224
Morgan freeman:
<i>paul the penguin</i>

09:53.226 --> 09:55.226
<i>later emptied</i>
<i>his bank account,</i>

09:55.228 --> 09:58.129
<i>slapped his wife</i>
<i>and killed himself.</i>

09:58.131 --> 10:00.532
<i>He was my best friend.</i>

10:03.970 --> 10:06.605
Rallo, why would you
throw away all your art?

10:06.607 --> 10:08.473
Even our family
portrait.

10:09.909 --> 10:11.443
Look, the only reason

10:11.445 --> 10:13.244
I haven't been
honest with you is,

10:13.246 --> 10:15.580
well, you're just
not good at anything.

10:15.582 --> 10:17.082
No kid is.

10:17.084 --> 10:19.918
So you're saying
I suck at everything?

10:19.920 --> 10:21.987
Aw, baby, don't look
at it that way.

10:21.989 --> 10:24.289
It's not just you,
it's all kids.

10:24.291 --> 10:26.591
They all suck
at everything.

10:26.593 --> 10:28.593
Now, where's
my magic umbrella?

10:28.595 --> 10:30.261
Thank you, freddy.

10:30.263 --> 10:31.596
Hang on!

10:31.598 --> 10:34.432
♪Every Boy And Girl You Know

10:34.434 --> 10:36.434
♪Is Worthless
From their head to toe ♪

10:36.436 --> 10:40.138
♪It's Like A Bedbug
Mated with an invalid ♪

10:40.140 --> 10:42.273
♪They're Frail And Weak
And short in height ♪

10:42.275 --> 10:44.275
♪Their Hands Too Small,
Their brains not right ♪

10:44.277 --> 10:47.979
♪It's Not Your Fault You Suck,
You're just a kid ♪

10:47.981 --> 10:51.950
♪You're As Worthless
As a recent song by sting ♪

10:51.952 --> 10:56.287
♪Yes, Kids Suck
At Everything ♪

10:56.289 --> 10:58.657
So, kids are just
useless wastes of space?

10:58.659 --> 11:00.959
Now it sounds like
you're getting it.

11:00.961 --> 11:03.995
But I'm sure
you're not.

11:03.997 --> 11:08.299
♪If You're Tiny Brain
Remembers Just one thing ♪

11:08.301 --> 11:15.974
♪Kids Suck At Everything.

11:15.976 --> 11:19.144
This song does not apply
to asian kids.

11:19.146 --> 11:20.712
CLEVELAND:
I found it!

11:22.815 --> 11:24.883
Aw, this is so cool.

11:24.885 --> 11:27.485
Wandering around an
abandoned amusement park

11:27.487 --> 11:29.487
just like I've always
nightmared about.

11:29.489 --> 11:31.189
Look-- the carousel!

11:31.191 --> 11:35.026
And it's exactly as much fun
as when a carousel moves.

11:35.028 --> 11:36.895
Hey, a funhouse mirror.

11:36.897 --> 11:38.663
(All Laughing)

11:38.665 --> 11:40.732
Look at that.
Look at what
freaks we are.

11:40.734 --> 11:43.868
(Rhythmically):
I'm funky junction fred
and I love to dance.

11:43.870 --> 11:47.205
I got a big ol' head
full of mildew and ants.

11:47.207 --> 11:48.506
(Laughs)

11:48.508 --> 11:50.842
Oh, stop, stop,
cleveland, stop.

11:50.844 --> 11:53.511
Oh, seriously...
You are making me horny.

11:53.513 --> 11:54.913
Me, too.

11:54.915 --> 11:56.915
Hey, fellas, check it out--
the rotor.

11:56.917 --> 11:57.982
Get on.

12:02.054 --> 12:05.757
Let's see if I remember how to
do this from my carny days.

12:10.196 --> 12:11.696
LESTER: Welcome to the rotor,
please keep your hands

12:11.698 --> 12:13.598
and arms inside the ride
at all times-- here we go.

12:15.868 --> 12:20.405
CLEVELAND: Hooray!
This is the funnest way to get
forced up against a wall.

12:20.407 --> 12:23.775
Get ready, the floor's
about to drop out.

12:24.744 --> 12:26.244
Hey, check it out.

12:26.246 --> 12:28.279
(Grunting)

12:28.281 --> 12:32.117
Aah! I want to lie on you
naked in front of
a roaring fire

12:32.119 --> 12:34.719
and sexily beckon donna over,
but then she says,

12:34.721 --> 12:36.921
"who knows how many people
have done it on that rug?"

12:36.923 --> 12:38.456
And I say, "come on,
when's the next time

12:38.458 --> 12:40.391
we'll be in yellowstone?"

12:40.393 --> 12:43.228
I want me some of that
sweet bonding action.

12:43.230 --> 12:44.629
Cannonball!

12:46.732 --> 12:49.400
(All Laughing)

12:49.402 --> 12:50.568
The bros are back.

12:50.570 --> 12:51.770
Guys, group picture.

12:51.772 --> 12:52.771
Everybody get together.

12:52.773 --> 12:55.140
(Grunting)

13:00.246 --> 13:02.747
ALL:
Cheese!

13:02.749 --> 13:03.948
ALL:
Aw, shucks!

13:03.950 --> 13:05.984
All right, let's
go get our phones.

13:05.986 --> 13:07.652
Lester, that's your cue.

13:07.654 --> 13:09.420
Jump out and turn
this thing off.

13:09.422 --> 13:11.089
Oh, boy.

13:11.091 --> 13:11.990
(All Yelling)
CLEVELAND:
I can't see.

13:11.992 --> 13:13.625
You guys all got worried looks

13:13.627 --> 13:14.959
on your faces, too?

13:14.961 --> 13:16.427
TIM: Yep.
LESTER: Uh-huh.

13:16.429 --> 13:17.829
HOLT:
Nope, doing my nicholson.

13:22.001 --> 13:25.303
I got to find a way to prove
to mama that I'm not a baby.

13:25.305 --> 13:28.773
Well, you could wear a diaper
and suck on a pacifier.

13:28.775 --> 13:30.275
That's a terrible idea.

13:30.277 --> 13:32.277
That would make me appear
more like a baby.

13:32.279 --> 13:33.812
Okay, okay,
how about this?

13:33.814 --> 13:36.614
You roll around in the crib,
crying for your mommy.

13:36.616 --> 13:38.349
Y'all are just screwing
with me, aren't you?

13:38.351 --> 13:40.451
Yeah, we are,
you little baby.

13:40.453 --> 13:41.786
(Groans)

13:41.788 --> 13:43.621
I'm starting to worry
about cleveland.

13:43.623 --> 13:45.623
He never misses
hot dinner night.

13:45.625 --> 13:46.858
(Doorbell Rings)

13:46.860 --> 13:48.793
Hello, donna.

13:48.795 --> 13:51.329
Tim hasn't come home
so I thought maybe

13:51.331 --> 13:53.031
he was here
having sex with you.

13:53.033 --> 13:56.868
And lester was supposed to be
home to play "folds o' gold,"

13:56.870 --> 13:58.703
A romantic treasure hunt

13:58.705 --> 14:01.639
where I hide doubloons
in my body rolls.

14:01.641 --> 14:03.141
So, none of them came home?

14:03.143 --> 14:05.977
(Gasps) Do you think they
might all be together?

14:05.979 --> 14:07.478
Maybe with holt, too?

14:07.480 --> 14:08.980
Who knows?

14:08.982 --> 14:11.816
I went ahead
and got myself started.

14:11.818 --> 14:13.651
You need help
finding those guys?

14:13.653 --> 14:15.153
I'll help--
I can do it.

14:15.155 --> 14:18.156
Okay, rallo, you can be
mama's big boy helper

14:18.158 --> 14:20.725
and make
some phone calls.

14:20.727 --> 14:23.228
Come on, ladies,
let's go search for real.

14:23.230 --> 14:25.563
If kids sucked at everything,

14:25.565 --> 14:26.698
could they track down

14:26.700 --> 14:28.933
their fat stepdad?

14:30.502 --> 14:33.338
Don't be scared, rallo--
just listen to some music.

14:33.340 --> 14:36.674
(Hip Hop beat plays)
♪The Wheels On The Bus
Go round and round ♪

14:36.676 --> 14:38.243
♪Round And Round

14:38.245 --> 14:41.045
♪The Wheels On The Bus
Go round and round ♪

14:41.047 --> 14:42.614
♪All Through Town...

14:51.390 --> 14:54.058
Hey, no one under 18.

14:54.060 --> 14:55.560
I'm looking for my stepdad.

14:55.562 --> 14:57.028
Oh, okay.

14:57.030 --> 14:58.863
Here's your drink tickets.

14:58.865 --> 15:02.367
Little man,
what you doing here?

15:02.369 --> 15:04.535
I'm looking for cleveland
and his idiot friends.

15:04.537 --> 15:06.738
I thought maybe they'd be
here, 'cause men get sick

15:06.740 --> 15:08.873
of looking at the same
boobies all the time.

15:08.875 --> 15:10.275
I haven't seen him, chief.

15:10.277 --> 15:11.743
Did you check the facebook?

15:11.745 --> 15:13.778
Holt's always
posting stupid stuff

15:13.780 --> 15:15.880
on there and this
place got internet.

15:15.882 --> 15:18.416
Fifi, when you're done
with that wee-wee,

15:18.418 --> 15:21.319
come over here and help
pee wee with the free wee-fee.

15:22.221 --> 15:24.622
Hey, I want
some grossness.

15:24.624 --> 15:27.625
Well, holt did
friend-request me a year ago.

15:27.627 --> 15:30.895
Guess I could add him and
unfriend him before he knows.

15:30.897 --> 15:34.098
Hey, four hours ago,
he posted a photo.

15:34.100 --> 15:35.633
Look at that dumb-ass
cleveland

15:35.635 --> 15:37.635
dressed as a saloon floozy.

15:37.637 --> 15:40.939
They must be at the old-timey
photo booth at funky junction.

15:40.941 --> 15:42.740
Remember how many times
I promised

15:42.742 --> 15:43.975
to take you there
and I didn't?

15:43.977 --> 15:45.410
That was fun, right?

15:45.412 --> 15:46.744
Can you take me there now?

15:46.746 --> 15:47.979
I can drop you off.

15:47.981 --> 15:49.247
You got five for gas?

15:49.249 --> 15:50.315
Yeah.

15:50.317 --> 15:52.383
Let's roll.

15:55.254 --> 15:56.621
I can do this all night.

15:56.623 --> 15:58.122
My mom used to put me
in the dryer.

15:58.124 --> 16:00.325
This is all your fault
for bringing us here.

16:00.327 --> 16:01.960
Oh yeah?
Well, you're the one

16:01.962 --> 16:03.661
who jumped
on the ride like a...

16:03.663 --> 16:04.963
Don't you say it.

16:04.965 --> 16:06.464
...Crumb bum.

16:06.466 --> 16:07.465
(Both Gasp)

16:07.467 --> 16:08.633
Only my people

16:08.635 --> 16:09.834
can use that word.

16:09.836 --> 16:11.803
(Both Grunting with effort)

16:11.805 --> 16:15.606
Can you move
your face a little closer?

16:15.608 --> 16:17.175
Uh, guys...

16:18.510 --> 16:20.411
Aw, gross...
(Retching)

16:26.452 --> 16:29.587
Aah! My own vomit is
the grossest kind.

16:30.522 --> 16:32.156
I was wrong.

16:32.158 --> 16:34.625
(Tires Screech)

16:34.627 --> 16:37.962
Man, this place looks scary.

16:37.964 --> 16:39.530
A'ight, see you later.

16:39.532 --> 16:40.665
(Engine Revs, tires squeal)

16:40.667 --> 16:43.368
That man is not a good father.

16:43.370 --> 16:44.869
(Yelling In distance)

16:46.972 --> 16:48.806
Don't worry, cleveland,
I'm here.

16:48.808 --> 16:50.008
CLEVELAND: Rallo!
LESTER: Thank god.

16:50.010 --> 16:51.642
HOLT: Help us!

16:51.644 --> 16:54.645
Hi, rallo, I'm
your daddy's friend.

16:54.647 --> 16:56.147
Yeah, I know.

16:56.149 --> 16:59.117
Get in the control booth
and turn the ride off!

17:02.554 --> 17:04.989
Damn it.

17:04.991 --> 17:07.825
All right, hang on,
I'm gonna try something else.

17:07.827 --> 17:09.827
What grade are you in now?

17:09.829 --> 17:12.230
Stop trying
to make conversation.

17:18.003 --> 17:21.072
(Grunting)

17:23.575 --> 17:26.577
All right, guys, grab onto
the rope and I'll pull you up.

17:32.418 --> 17:34.352
Aah!

17:34.354 --> 17:37.021
None of you are worth this!

17:37.023 --> 17:41.426
TIM:
So, do you have a girlfriend?

17:43.429 --> 17:45.363
Donna!

17:45.365 --> 17:47.365
I knew you'd come
crawling back.

17:47.367 --> 17:50.368
I'm looking for cleveland--
although I doubt he's here.

17:50.370 --> 17:52.103
He can see these
anytime he wants.

17:52.105 --> 17:54.906
He ain't here-- he's
at funky junction.

17:54.908 --> 17:56.707
Cleveland's
at the amusement park?

17:56.709 --> 17:58.209
How do you know?

17:58.211 --> 17:59.877
'Cause rallo was here
looking for him.

17:59.879 --> 18:01.112
I gave him a ride.

18:01.114 --> 18:02.547
I hope he found him.

18:02.549 --> 18:04.215
You just left him
at the park alone?

18:04.217 --> 18:06.217
(Shrieks)
All by himself?

18:06.219 --> 18:09.053
That's what "alone" means,
you dumb stripper.

18:09.055 --> 18:11.756
Y'all need church!

18:11.758 --> 18:13.257
(Tires Screech)

18:13.259 --> 18:15.293
(Yelling)

18:17.062 --> 18:18.963
Rallo, what are
you doing up there?

18:18.965 --> 18:20.565
I tried to save cleveland

18:20.567 --> 18:22.900
but I screwed up and broke
the control switch.

18:22.902 --> 18:25.269
It's okay, baby, I know
you tried your best.

18:25.271 --> 18:27.238
It just wasn't good enough.

18:27.240 --> 18:28.473
And do you know why?

18:28.475 --> 18:30.241
Because kids suck at every...

18:30.243 --> 18:31.409
Sing it!

18:31.411 --> 18:32.410
♪'Cause Kids Suck

18:32.412 --> 18:35.413
♪At Everything.

18:35.415 --> 18:37.782
Oh, yeah-- that's my jam.

18:37.784 --> 18:39.917
Now, if you were an adult,
you would have known

18:39.919 --> 18:42.086
to go over
and turn the power off.

18:42.088 --> 18:43.254
CLEVELAND:
Donna, hurry.

18:43.256 --> 18:45.623
There's so
much vomit.

18:45.625 --> 18:47.592
Oh, hell... Sparks.

18:47.594 --> 18:49.093
It's okay.

18:49.095 --> 18:50.828
As an adult, I know
the best way to put out

18:50.830 --> 18:53.164
an electrical fire is
with water.

18:55.501 --> 18:57.702
Donna, hurry!

19:08.447 --> 19:10.114
Help! Help!

19:10.116 --> 19:12.116
Some kid
set the park on fire!

19:12.118 --> 19:14.318
What is your
deal with kids?

19:14.320 --> 19:17.121
I'm sorry, donna,
this is all my fault.

19:17.123 --> 19:19.490
Except for the fire,
which is your fault,

19:19.492 --> 19:21.692
and what's probably
going to kill us.

19:21.694 --> 19:23.794
(Yelling)

19:23.796 --> 19:25.663
(Screams)

19:25.665 --> 19:26.731
(Yelling)

19:35.841 --> 19:37.041
(Groaning)

19:37.043 --> 19:38.476
We're saved.

19:38.478 --> 19:41.312
Oh, thank god,
it was getting pretty...

19:41.314 --> 19:43.481
Hot in cleveland.

19:43.483 --> 19:44.549
DONNA:
Dumb.

19:47.653 --> 19:50.388
So, you broke into
an abandoned amusement park,

19:50.390 --> 19:53.224
then you, a five-year-old,
tried to rescue them,

19:53.226 --> 19:55.526
and you set
the whole place on fire.

19:55.528 --> 19:57.995
To prove a point to my son
that kids suck at everything.

19:57.997 --> 20:00.064
You all suck at everything.

20:00.066 --> 20:04.001
Rescuing people is our job--
we're the heroes.

20:04.003 --> 20:07.004
Haven't you seen denis leary's
award-losing  <i>rescue me?</i>

20:07.006 --> 20:09.173
Heard it's good.
No.
I meant to check it out.

20:09.175 --> 20:11.842
See, the thing about the show
is it gets enough right

20:11.844 --> 20:14.612
that the stuff
it gets wrong...

20:16.048 --> 20:18.683
Hey, Mr. Fireman,
"f u!"

20:18.685 --> 20:21.352
Rallo!
No, mama, "f u."

20:21.354 --> 20:22.587
Did you hear
what rallo said?

20:22.589 --> 20:24.922
Ooh, gonna get it.

20:27.693 --> 20:29.760
Why, you little...!

20:29.762 --> 20:32.530
You saved our lives.

20:32.532 --> 20:35.099
You knew I'd try
to beat the crap out of you

20:35.101 --> 20:38.035
if you punched me
in the old fire extinguisher.

20:38.037 --> 20:39.937
You're a hero, kid.

20:39.939 --> 20:42.073
A real... Hero...

20:42.075 --> 20:43.741
You hear that, mama?

20:43.743 --> 20:45.042
I sure did.

20:45.044 --> 20:46.377
Hey, little guy,
would you like

20:46.379 --> 20:48.246
to ring the bell
on my fire truck?

20:48.248 --> 20:50.348
Yes.

20:51.550 --> 20:53.884
I want to ring
the bell, too.

20:53.886 --> 20:54.585
(Imitating Siren)
